3.Given an array integer arr[] , representing the values of coins arranged in a row.
Platform : GeeksForGeeks
SOURCE CODE :class Solution {
    public int coin(int[] arr) {
        int i = 0;
        int j = arr.length - 1;

        while (i < j) {

            // Player 1
            if (arr[i] >= arr[j])
                i++;
            else
                j--;

            if (i >= j)
                break;

            // Player 2
            if (arr[i] >= arr[j])
                i++;
            else
                j--;
        }

        return arr[i];
    }
}
Link : https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/problems/last-coin-in-a-game-of-alternates/1
