    5.Given an array arr and an element k. The task is to find the count of elements in the array that appear more than n/k times and n is length of arr.
Platform : GeeksForGeeks
SOURCE CODE : class Solution {
    public int countElements(int[] arr, int k) {
        int n = arr.length;
        HashMap<Integer, Integer> map = new HashMap<>();
        for (int num : arr) {
            map.put(num, map.getOrDefault(num, 0) + 1);
        }
        int count = 0;
        for (int freq : map.values()) {
            if (freq > n / k) {
                count++;
            }
        }
        return count;
    }
}
    https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/problems/count-element-occurences/1
    6.Given a positive integer n, find if it is a power of 3. A number is said to be a power of 3 if it can be expressed as 3x for some non-negative integer x.
Platform : GeeksForGeeks
SOURCE CODE : class Solution {
    public boolean isPowerOfThree(int n) {
        if (n <= 0) return false;
        while (n % 3 == 0) {
            n /= 3;
        }
        return n == 1;
    }
}
    Link : https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/problems/check-a-integer-is-power-of-3-or-not3850/1
